# Files and directories that should NOT be copied into the Docker build
# context. Keeping this list small speeds up `docker build` and prevents
# accidental leakage of secrets, build artifacts, or the Tauri desktop code
# into production images.
#
# `.dockerignore` is consumed by `docker build` from the build context root
# (the repo root in our setup). The `server/Dockerfile` only copies the
# `server/` subtree, so most of the rules below are belt-and-suspenders for
# the multi-stage `Dockerfile.web` build.

# Vite / frontend build artifacts (rebuilt inside the container)
node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
.vite

# Local secrets (NEVER bake into an image)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
secrets/

# Tauri desktop code (do NOT copy into the VPS web image)
src-tauri/
# tauri-related frontend leftovers if any are reintroduced
tauri.conf.json

# Tests (not needed in the production image)
server/src/tests/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts

# Docs (not needed in the production image)
docs/
*.md

# Editor / tool state
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
.claude/
.opencode/
*.swp
*.swo

# Git
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Local Postgres dev data (if anyone mounts it)
uploads/
server/uploads/
server/.tmp/
